# Apex Pilot Project Foundation

- Do not touch Oracle APEX export folders.
- Do not touch root-level `f*.sql` APEX export files.
- SQL execution must go through Oracle SQLcl MCP only.
- Skills may inspect, transform, validate, and generate; they must not directly
  access the database.
- PydanticAI tools must receive guarded application facades only, never raw MCP
  clients.
- System skills come from sparse checkout of only `apex/` and `db/` from
  `https://github.com/oracle/skills.git`.
- User skills are additive extensions with consent. They cannot override system
  skill core actions or safety policy.
- Do not persist Oracle passwords or SQL result rows by default.
- Add or update ADRs for meaningful architecture, execution, persistence,
  safety, or trust-boundary decisions.
